  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.1.0 (6547691 2022-02-21T00:27:15.958524+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge build\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (M1)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nam trying to build a foundry project that uses the [solidity-BigNumber](https://github.com/firoorg/solidity-BigNumber) library, which uses a lot of asm under the hood, specifically the `msize` instruction. when i run `forge build` i get the following error\r\n\r\n```\r\nSyntaxError: The msize instruction cannot be used when the Yul optimizer is activated because it can change its semantics. Either disable the Yul optimizer or do not use the instruction.\r\n```\r\n\r\nmy `foundry.toml` looks like the following:\r\n```\r\n[default]\r\nsrc = 'src'\r\nout = 'out'\r\nlibs = ['lib']\r\nremappings = ['ds-test/=lib/ds-test/src']\r\noptimizer = true\r\n\r\n[optimizer_details]\r\nyul = false\r\n```\r\n\r\nit seems as if forge is not respecting the `yul = false` option?",
